ndiana|Kokomo]], and the western suburbs of [[Indianapolis]]. The incumbent is Republican [[Jim Baird (American politician)|Jim Baird]], who was elected with 64.1% of the vote in 2018.<ref name=\"HPVT\"/>\n\n===Republican primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Declared=====\n* Jeffrey Alberts<ref name=\"IN04\">{{cite web |last1=Bangert |first1=Dave |title=Candidates in, candidates out as crowded Tippecanoe Co. primaries set |url=https://www.jconline.com/story/news/2020/02/07/candidates-in-candidates-out-crowded-tippecanoe-co-primaries-set/4667424002/ |website=Lafayette Journal & Courier |date=February 7, 2020}}</ref>\n* [[Jim Baird (American politician)|Jim Baird]], incumbent U.S. Representative\n\n====Primary results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Republican primary results\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Jeffrey Alberts\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Jim Baird (American politician)|Jim Baird]] (incumbent)\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = \n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Democratic primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Declared=====\n* Ben Frederick<ref name=\"IN04\"/>\n* Joe Mackey, retired machinist<ref>{{cite web |title=LISTEN: Interview With 4th District Democratic Challenger Joe Mackey |url=https://www.wfyi.org/news/articles/listen-interview-with-4th-district-democratic-challenger-joe-mackey |website=wfyi |date=October 4, 2019}}</ref> \n* Howard Pollchik<ref name=\"IN04\"/>\n* Veronikka Ziol, transgender rights activist<ref name=\"IN04\"/>\n\n====Primary results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Democratic primary results\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Ben Frederick\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = 