rooks2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.indystar.com/story/news/politics/elections/2019/06/14/susan-brooks-indiana-republican-congress-will-not-run-election-2020/1454213001/|title=Exclusive: Indiana Republican Susan Brooks will not seek re-election to Congress|last1=Groppe|first1=Maureen|date=June 14, 2019|newspaper=The Indianapolis Star|accessdate=June 14, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Republican primary===\n=====Declared=====\n*Kent W. Abernathy, former commissioner of  Indiana's Bureau of Motor Vehicles<ref>{{cite web |last1=Erdody |first1=Lindsey |title=Former BMV commissioner running for Congress |url=https://www.ibj.com/articles/former-bmv-commissioner-running-for-congress |website=Indianapolis Business Journal |accessdate=October 8, 2019 |date=October 7, 2019}}</ref>\n*Andrew Bales, retired teacher<ref>{{Cite web|title=Anderson Native running for GOP nomination in 5th District|url=https://www.heraldbulletin.com/news/local_news/anderson-native-running-for-gop-nomination-in-th-district/article_e738da7a-1129-11ea-b88f-e3d64ef58054.html |accessdate=27 November 2019 |date=November 27, 2019}}</ref>\n* Micah Beckwith, pastor<ref>{{cite web|url=https://thetimes24-7.com/Content/News/Local-News/Article/Noblesville-resident-running-for-Congress/1/1/62428|title=Noblesville resident running for Congress|website=The Noblesville Times|publisher=Sagamore News Media}}</ref>\n* Carl Brizzi, former [[Marion County, Indiana#Politics|Marion County prosecutor]]<ref>https://www.wthr.com/article/former-prosecutor-carl-brizzi-files-run-congress</ref>\n*Allen Davidson, highway engineer<ref name=\"IN05c\">{{cite web |last1=Lange |first1=Kaitlin |title=2020 Elections: Here's who is running in Indiana's 5th Congressional District |url=https://www.indystar.com/story/news/politics/2019/10/11/2020-elections-who-running-indiana-5th-congressional-district-susan-brooks-retirement/3930392002/ |website=Indianpolis Star |date=October 11, 2019}}</ref>\n*Chuck Dietzen, physician and founder of Timmy Global Healt