e|first1=Kaitlin|date=July 11, 2019|accessdate=July 11, 2019|publisher=The Indianapolis Star}}</ref>\n* Andy Jacobs Jr., [[Marion County, Indiana|Marion County]] deputy prosecutor and son of [[Andrew Jacobs Jr.]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Spehler |first1=Dan |title=IN Focus: Andy Jacobs running for Congress in 5th district |url=https://fox59.com/2019/12/01/in-focus-andy-jacobs-running-for-congress-in-5th-district/ |website=FOX 59 |accessdate=December 2, 2019 |date=December 1, 2019}}</ref>\n* Dee Thornton, corporate consultant and nominee for [[Indiana's 5th congressional district]]<nowiki/> in [[2018 United States House of Representatives elections in Indiana#District 5|2018]]<ref name=\"IN05d2\" />\n*Ralph Spelbring, frequent candidate<ref name=\"IN05c\"/>\n=====Declined=====\n* [[Carey Hamilton]], state representative<ref>{{cite tweet|last=Clearfield|first=Alex|user=AlexClearfield|number=1140962771032518656|title=Scooplet in #IN05: state Rep. Carey Hamilton (D) tells me she is not running, saying it's \"not the right time\" for her or her family. She represents northeast Marion County. Comes on the heels of Indy Mayor Greg Ballard pondering run.|date=June 18, 2019|accessdate=June 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\n====Endorsements====\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Jennifer Christie\n| list =\n* Blue America<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blueamerica.crooksandliars.com/2019/09/15/this-mother-of-4-understands-what-it-will-take-to-win-back-a-red-seat/|title=This Mother Of 4 Understands What It Will Take To Win Back A Red Seat|website=Blue America|first=Howie|last=Klein|date=15 September 2019|accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n* DUH! Demand Universal Healthcare<ref name=\"duh\"/>\n}}\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Christina Hale\n| list =\n;Local officials\n* Keith Potts, councilmember of [[Indianapolis City-County Council]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Potts |first1=Keith |title=During this unprecedented time, it's clear that what we need in Congress is calm, competent leadership with a track reco