can primary results\n}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = [[Larry Bucshon]] (incumbent)\n| party = Republican Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = \n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===Democratic primary===\n====Candidates====\n=====Declared=====\n*Ron Drake, attorney<ref name=\"IN08\">{{cite web |last1=Langhorne |first1=Thomas B. |title=Trio of Democrats face uphill charge against Bucshon |url=https://www.courierpress.com/story/news/2020/02/16/trio-democrat-candidates-face-uphill-charge-against-larry-bucshon/4760075002/ |website=Courier & Press |date=February 16, 2020}}</ref>\n*Thomasina Marsili, registered emergency medical technician<ref name=\"IN08\"/>\n*Mike Webster, computer distributions manager for [[SABIC]]<ref name=\"IN08\"/>\n\n=====Declined=====\n*[[John R. Gregg]], former [[speaker of the Indiana House of Representatives]] and nominee for [[Governor of Indiana]] in [[Indiana gubernatorial election, 2012|2012]] and [[Indiana gubernatorial election, 2016|2016]]<ref name=\"IN08\"/>\n*Jonathan Weinzapfel, former mayor of [[Evansville, Indiana|Evansville]]<ref name=\"IN08\"/>\n*Charlie Wyatt, mayor of [[Boonville, Indiana|Boonville]]<ref name=\"IN08\"/>\n\n====Primary results====\n{{Election box begin no change\n| title = Democratic primary results\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Ron Drake\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Thomasina Marsili\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n| candidate = Mike Webster\n| party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| votes = \n| percentage = \n}}\n{{Election box total no change\n| votes = \n| percentage = 100.0\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===General election===\n===